OL,5,GIt is no exaggeration to say that HM
OL,6,GQueen Elizabeth II was the first
OL,7,Gmonarch of the television age.
OL,9,FIn 1952 television in Britain was
OL,10,Falready setting out on the path which
OL,11,Fwould rapidly turn it from a scientific
OL,12,Fwonder or distraction for a minority to
OL,13,Fa vital part of everyday life.
OL,15,FWhen George VI died, only three
OL,16,Ftransmitters were in service  covering
OL,17,FLondon, the Midlands and much of
OL,18,Fnorthern England.
OL,3,CThe role of big Royal occasions in the
OL,4,Cdevelopment of television
OL,22,                                  G1/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
