PN,35502
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F355A1667072492
OL,5,FThe transmitter covering central
OL,6,FScotland was weeks away from opening.
OL,7,FSpecial arrangements were put in place
OL,8,Fso if could temporarily come into
OL,9,Foperation to broadcast the King's
OL,10,Ffuneral but it is unclear just how many
OL,11,Faround Glasgow and Edinburgh were
OL,12,Factually able to watch.
OL,14,FHowever, it was the decision to
OL,15,Fbroadcast the Coronation in 1953 which
OL,16,Ftruly marked the start of the
OL,17,Ftelevision age in Britain. More
OL,18,Ftransmitters were brought into service
OL,19,Frapidly to try to ensure as many people
OL,20,Fas possible were able to watch.
OL,3,CThe role of big Royal occasions in the
OL,4,Cdevelopment of television
OL,22,                                  G2/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
